  '<h4 class="criteria-heading">KEY INCLUSION CRITERIA:</h4><ul class="criteria-list"><li>Patients &ge;60 years</li><li>Symptomatic, chronic systolic heart failure of ischaemic aetiology</li><li>Ejection fraction &le;40% (NYHA class III/IV) or &le;35% (NYHA class II)</li><li>Patients receiving optimal therapy at least 2 weeks before randomisation</li></ul><div class="study-schema"><h4>STUDY SCHEMA:</h4><img src="assets/images/corona.study-design.jpg" style="width:639px; height:auto;" alt="Study"/></div><h4>PRIMARY ENDPOINT:</h4><ul><li>Time to the first occurrence of cardiovascular death, non-fatal MI, or non-fatal stroke</li></ul><h4>SELECTED SECONDARY ENDPOINTS:</h4><ul><li>Individual components of the primary endpoint</li><li>Number of hospitalisations for cardiovascular causes</li></ul>',
